      "params": {
        "title": "How Butter Is Made",
        "meaning": "버터가 만들어지는 진짜 과정을 따라가는 이야기예요. 색칠된 단어를 누르면 설명을 듣고, 🎙로 선생님과 이야기도 나눠보세요.",
        "words": [
          "raw",
          "solid",
          "separate",
          "beat",
          "churn",
          "break down",
          "fat",
          "droplet"
        ],
        "wordExplanations": {
          "raw": "Raw means not cooked. Butter is made from raw cow's milk.",
          "solid": "Solid means hard and firm, with a clear shape. Butter is solid. Milk is not.",
          "separate": "Separate means to take things apart, so they are not together anymore.",
          "beat": "Beat means to hit something many, many times.",
          "churn": "Churn means to beat or shake cream until it becomes butter.",
          "break down": "Break down means to break something into small pieces.",
          "fat": "Fat is the white or yellow oily part of food. Butter is mostly fat.",
          "droplet": "A droplet is a very, very small drop of liquid."
        },
        "voiceTalks": {
          "raw": "Target word: raw (= not cooked). In the story, butter is made from raw cow's milk. Ask ONE easy question, e.g.: Is raw food cooked? or: What raw food do you know?",
          "solid": "Target word: solid (= hard and firm, with a clear shape). In the story, milk turns into a block of solid butter. Ask ONE easy question, e.g.: Is milk solid? Is ice solid?",
          "separate": "Target word: separate (= to take things apart). In the story, a separator separates the fatty cream from the milk. Ask ONE easy question, e.g.: What does the separator separate?",
          "beat": "Target word: beat (= to hit many times). In the story, the cream is beaten in a churner. Ask this book question: What is the closest meaning of beat - to boil, or to hit?",
          "churn": "Target word: churn (= to beat or shake cream into butter). Ask ONE easy question, e.g.: What do we get when we churn cream?",
          "break down": "Target phrase: break down (= to break into small pieces). In the story, churning breaks down the thin cover of each fat droplet. Ask ONE easy question, e.g.: What breaks down the covers of the droplets?",
          "fat": "Target word: fat (= the oily part of food). In the story, fat droplets join together and become butter. Ask ONE easy question, e.g.: Which foods have a lot of fat?",
          "droplet": "Target word: droplet (= a very small drop of liquid). Ask ONE easy question, e.g.: Is a droplet big or small? Where can you see droplets?"
        },
